<p>There&#8217;s always plenty of oil in a recession. You almost can&#8217;t give it away. But lowered prices do not mean that there&#8217;s no peak oil any more than heightened prices mean there is.</p>
<p>Anyone who does not believe in peak oil at this point has no concept of the term &#8216;finite resource&#8217;. As such, Alexander Cockburn&#8217;s musings about oil might get him a paycheck, but for the rest of us, what he has to say is about as reliable and useful as what my 8 year-old daughter has to say about it.</p>
